text:
Fifth Avenue at S.E. corner of 85th Street, showing "The Fifth Avenue", one of the first modern apartment houses on Fifth Avenue.
It has since been demolished and replaced by a larger, more modern, building.
About 1925.

Brown Brothers, photographer.

folder: Central Park & Transverse roads., Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park: Transverse Road: The 85th Street roadway thru the Park after removal of the 86th Street crosstown car tracks by the W. P. A.

Both views are westward and show apartment houses on the west side of Central Park West; the photographers vantage point being under the East Drive in No. 1 and slightly east of the West Drive in No. 2.

January 19, 1937
Views: 1 and 2

W. P. A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Transverse roads.
